    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "> it's probably not really an issue IMO, although a subset was already set with objectIDs, which you said was insufficient for segment\r\n\r\nWhat I meant by a subset was to pass an object made from `hit` with some properties omitted like, for example, `image_url, description, ...` that won't be used in the `insights` middleware.\r\n\r\nIt could bloat the html size and might be an issue in case of SSR. Even if so, they can omit some properties to avoid the issue.",
    "created_at": "2021-03-08T16:11:37Z",
    "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/pull/4670#issuecomment-792865198",
